column180: I see there are quite a few questions about Andrew Cuomo. It doesn't escape me there has been a concerted effort to smear his name wildly. For me, this is a backfire. He was the leading voice to give calm during the Covid terror which Trump rightfully should have been blamed for, but he is just ONE man. One. Every Governor needed to have a playbook on what to do and Cuomo stood above the rest - and suddenly he became a threat to too many in, by and large, commanding a nation. I fell from Progressive admiration after watching them collectively want to destroy him. The thought of Cynthia Nixon, who literally her only job has been actress, command the financial capital of the Americas, who had a Twitter meltdown over room temperature settings at debates... good lord, half the city would have been dead and a litany of people would have had to cover for her. Progressives have disappointed me... greatly.

column180: Do not like ranked voting. I understand how it works, but I feel some voters don't understand. I've worked several years as a Coordinator for a site during election time and my observations about voters, they lack understanding of the voting process in and of itself. Educating voters is a MUST in this country. Understanding the ballot; voting site; if they haven't voted in 4 years, am I still registered to vote; only voting during predidential elections not local and how important it is to vote other than presidential. A host of valuable information that people do not vote. I believe that is the reason citizens don't vote. We are letting our citizens down and not informing them how important it is to vote. How it helps their communities for funding. Schools, sanitation, infrastructure to keep their communities viable.
